==English==

===Noun===
'''salon des refusés'''

===Etymology===
From the French, meaning "room, or gallery, of the refused [works]".

From Emile Zola--
     ''Dans un de ces anciens '''Salons des Refusés''', que l'âme charitable de Napoléon III ouvrait aux révoltés et aux égarés de la peinture ?''
     trans: "In one of those old '''Salons des Refusés''', which the charitable soul of Napoleon III opened to the rebels and vagabonds of painting"

===Meaning===
A place, or figuratively, a work, which hosts a collection of artists/writers works which have been hitherto refused publication or exhibition by any source.

